The paper focuses on developing a pre-trainable generic representation for visual-linguistic tasks, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of these two fields. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various downstream tasks, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories.
